A teenager, Alade Mujeed, was on Monday arraigned in an Ile-Ife Magistrates’ Court in Osun for allegedly stealing an Infinix Hot5 mobile phone worth N35,000 in an examination hall. The 18-year-old is standing trial on a two-count charge of entering and stealing. The Prosecutor, Insp Sunday Osanyintuyi, told the court that the defendant committed the offence on Sept. 13 at about 12:00 p.m. at Oduduwa College Examination Hall, Ile-Ife. Osanyintuyi said that the defendant entered the examination hall with the intent to commit a felony therein. ALSO READ: Lalong signs N177.3bn 2020 appropriation bill into law He added that the defendant opened the bag of one Giwa Samuel and stole the phone. According to him, the offence contravenes Sections 383, 390(9) and 413 of the Criminal Code of Osun, 2002. Scavenger jailed three months for stealing N2,000 Three guards in court for allegedly stealing customer’s… Court sentences hairdresser to three months in prison for… Court orders applicant to sweep court premises for stealing… The defendant, however, pleaded not guilty to the charge. The Defence Counsel, Mr Kehinde Adegbite, prayed the court to grant bail to his client in the most liberal terms. The council pledged that his client would not jump bail, but would provide substantial sureties. The Magistrate, Joseph Owolawi, granted bail to the defendant in the sum of N100,000 with one surety in like sum. Owolawi added that the surety must swear to an affidavit of means and reside within the court’s jurisdiction. He said the surety’s address must be verified in addition to providing three recent passport photographs. The magistrate adjourned the case till Jan. 7, 2020, for hearing. (NAN) SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE
